{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-awesome-timeline-js","path":"/rabbiabram/awesome-fortran/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Track Awesome List"}},"awesomeList":{"repo":"rabbiabram/awesome-fortran","descriptionHTML":"<div>Awesome list of Fortran libs</div>","description":"Awesome list of Fortran libs"},"awesomeListMeta":{"readmeParsedAt":"2021-06-29T11:15:31.510Z"},"allAwesomeItem":{"nodes":[{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Math Libs</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.imsl.com/products/imsl-fortran-libraries\">IMSL</a> - The IMSL Fortran Numerical Library is the standard for high performance computing commercial mathematics and statistics libraries</li>","updatedAt":"2020-05-12T19:46:31.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Math Libs</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.nag.co.uk/content/nag-library-fortran\">NAG Fortran Library</a> - Produced by experts for use in a variety of applications, the NAG Fortran Library has a global reputation for its excellence and, with hundreds of fully documented and tested routines, is the largest collection of mathematical and statistical algorithms available</li>","updatedAt":"2020-05-12T19:46:31.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Graphics Libraries</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.mps.mpg.de/dislin/\">DISLIN</a> - a high-level graphing and user-interface library.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-05-12T19:40:15.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Graphics Libraries</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://math.nist.gov/f90gl/\">f90gl</a> - public domain implementation of the official NIST Fortran 90 bindings for OpenGL.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-05-12T19:40:15.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Graphics Libraries</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/vmagnin/gtk-fortran/wiki\">gtk-fortran</a> - a cross-platform library to build Graphical User Interfaces (GUI) using <a href=\"https://www.gtk.org/\">GTK+</a>.  Very useful when combined with the <a href=\"https://glade.gnome.org/\">Glade</a> RAD tool.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-05-12T19:40:15.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Graphics Libraries</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.astro.caltech.edu/~tjp/pgplot/\">PGPLOT</a> - cross-platform scientific graphing library.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-05-12T19:40:15.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Math Libs</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.lrz.de/services/software/mathematik/gsl/fortran/index.html\">FGSL</a> - portable, object-based Fortran interface to the <a href=\"https://www.lrz.de/services/software/mathematik/gsl/\">GNU scientific library</a></li>","updatedAt":"2020-05-12T19:40:15.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Math Libs</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.ssisc.org/lis/index.en.html\">Lis</a> - a Library of Iterative Solvers for Linear Systems</li>","updatedAt":"2020-05-12T19:40:15.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Fortran Websites</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.fortran.com/\">The Fortran Company</a> - A home page of FORTRAN programming language.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-05-12T19:40:15.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Functional Libraries</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/wavebitscientific/functional-fortran\">Functional Fortran</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/wavebitscientific/functional-fortran\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">317</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":317,\"repo\":\"wavebitscientific/functional-fortran\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Functional programming for modern Fortran.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-04-22T01:47:52.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Testing</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://gitlab.com/everythingfunctional/vegetables\">Vegetables</a> - For a healthier code base, eat your vegetables</li>","updatedAt":"2019-03-28T16:33:44.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Web</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/mapmeld/fortran-machine\">Fortran Machine</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/mapmeld/fortran-machine\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">675</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":675,\"repo\":\"mapmeld/fortran-machine\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - An MVC web stack written in Fortran 90</li>","updatedAt":"2017-01-04T01:34:11.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Docker</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://hub.docker.com/r/baekjoon/onlinejudge-fortran/\">Unoficial Image</a> - docker image provided by @baekjoon</li>","updatedAt":"2016-11-30T07:09:30.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Graphics Libraries</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/szaghi/VTKFortran\">VTKFortran</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/szaghi/VTKFortran\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-r