h MPI extensions by developers from NASA and NGC TASC.  Uses parallel codes and object-oriented design.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-11-30T06:52:29.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Portability enabling</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/szaghi/PENF\">PENF</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/szaghi/PENF\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">31</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":31,\"repo\":\"szaghi/PENF\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Pure Fortran (2003+) library for ensuring codes portability.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-11-30T06:52:29.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Fortran Websites</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://fortrandev.wordpress.com/\">Fortran Dev</a> - Fortran development blog.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-01-14T05:44:48.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Fortran Videos</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=qUy8M10uZRU\">GNU FORTRAN Lesson 1</a> - Videos about the Fortran programming language.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-01-14T05:44:48.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Encoding-Decoding</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/szaghi/BeFoR64\">BeFoR64</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/szaghi/BeFoR64\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">16</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":16,\"repo\":\"szaghi/BeFoR64\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Base64 encoding/decoding library for FoRtran poor men. A KISS library for base64 encoding/decoding for modern (2003+) Fortran projects.</li>","updatedAt":"2015-02-02T11:27:59.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Command-Line parsing</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/szaghi/FLAP\">FLAP</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/szaghi/FLAP\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">110</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":110,\"repo\":\"szaghi/FLAP\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Fortran command Line Arguments Parser for poor men. A KISS library for building easily nice Command Line Interfaces (CLI) for modern (2003+) Fortran projects.</li>","updatedAt":"2015-02-02T11:27:59.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Command-Line parsing</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/cngilbreth/optionsf90\">options.f90</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/cngilbreth/optionsf90\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;ba